THE AREA IS CROWN LAND UNDER THE MANAGEMENT OF THE FORESTRY COMMISSION. THE CANNOP VALLEY CUTS INTO A PLEASANT WOODED AND HILLY AREA. THE CANNOP PONDS CONSTRUCTED FOR WATER POWER, OLD COALMINE SITES AND WASTE TIPS ARE EVIDENCE OF AN INDUSTRIAL PAST. FEW PEOPLE LIVE HERE BUT MANY ENJOY FREE ACCESS TO THE FOREST.
